lead_paragraph: Houston Texans All-Pro defensive end J.J. Watt underwent back surgery on Thursday and is expected to miss the remainder of the season, the NFL reported on its website.    Watt was placed on the injured reserve on Wednesday after re-injuring his back during last week's loss to New England.

headline.print_headline: Houston's Watt Faces Season on Sidelines After Back Surgery
